org.jcvi.jillion.core

Interface Rangeable

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    AceAssembledRead, AceAssembledReadBuilder, AsmAssembledRead, AsmAssembledReadBuilder, AssembledRead, AssembledReadBuilder<R>, CasPlacedRead, ConsensusAceTag, CoverageRegion<T>, PlacedContig, RangeableAceTag, TasmAssembledRead, TasmAssembledReadBuilder, TigrContigRead, TigrContigReadBuilder
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AceAssembledReadAdapter, DefaultAssembledRead, DefaultCasPlacedRead, DirectedRange, Range, Range.Builder, ReadAceTag

    public interface Rangeable
    Rangeable is a interface to denote that an object can be expressed as a Range.
    Author:
    dkatzel

      • intersects

        default boolean intersects(Rangeable target)
        Checks to see if the given Rangeable intersects this one. An empty range will never intersect any other range (even itself).
        Parameters:
        target - The Rangeable to check.
        Returns:
        true if the coordinates of the two ranges overlap each other in at least one point.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if target is null.
        Since:
        5.3

      • complement

        default List<Range> complement(Rangeable other)
        Get the List of Ranges that represents the this - other. This is similar to the Set of all coordinates that don't intersect.
        Parameters:
        other - the range to complement with.
        Returns:
        a List of Ranges; will never be null but may be empty.
        Since:
        5.3

      • complementOf

        default List<Range> complementOf(Collection<? extends Rangeable> others)
        Get the List of Ranges that represents this - others. This is similar to the Set of all coordinates in this Range that do not intersect the ranges in others. If the Ranges contained in others extends beyond this Range, then only coordinates within this Range are returned.
        Parameters:
        others - the ranges to complement from.
        Returns:
        a List of Ranges; may be empty if this Range is entirely covered by others.
        Throws:
        NullPointerException - if others is null.
        Since:
        5.3
